"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-08-Team-China-sets-Olympic-records-and-wins-historic-gold-on-day-12-1vTdvJXm3GE-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s been another exciting day at the Paris 2024 Olympics, with Team China setting new Olympic records and securing medals, including a historic first on day 12 of the Games, Wednesday, August 7.  For the first time in the country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s history, China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s acrobatic swim team clinched gold in artistic swimming, finishing with 996 points, a lead of nearly 82 points over the U.S. who took home silver.  Weightlifter Li Fabin took home another gold and set a new record in the 61kg weight class.  He set an Olympic snatch record by lifting 143 kilograms (315 pounds) on his final attempt, ending the competition with a massive score of 310.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Hou Zhihui also set a new Olympic weightlifting record for the clean-and-jerk in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 49kg weight class, lifting an impressive 206 kilograms (454 pounds).  In Taekwondo, China's Guo Qing won silver against the reigning Olympic champion in the women's flyweight division, Panipak Wongpattanakit from Thailand.  Team China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Deng Lijuan brought home a silver medal in a new sport debuting at Paris 2024, the sports climbing women's speed final.  Deng's time was only 0.08 seconds behind the winner, Aleksandra Miroslaw of Poland.  Feng Ziqi earned bronze in the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s freestyle wrestling match, beating Mongolia\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Otgonjargal Dolgorjav 6-4.  China also cemented its position in the women's field hockey final against the Netherlands, by defeating Belgium in a semifinal shoot-out.  In table tennis, Team China advanced to the semifinals in both the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s and women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s team quarterfinal matches.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"